Alpha Bank, Eurobank, National Bank of Greece, Opap Are Active

-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 
2011-03-11T16:06:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/hellenic-telecom-national-bank-of-greece-greek-stock-preview.html
  Greece ’s benchmark ASE Index rose
36.02, or 2.3 percent, to 1,580.90 at the 5:20 p.m. close in
Athens, its third straight day of gains. The gauge dropped 0.3
percent this week.  The FTSE/ASE 20 Index of the country’s biggest companies
gained 2.7 percent to 731.17. The Cyprus General Market Index
jumped 4.6 percent to 1,048.58.  The following shares were the most active in Athens trading
today. Symbols are in parentheses.    National Bank of Greece SA (ETE)   increased 3.8 percent
to 6.52 euros, gaining for a third day. German  Chancellor Angela Merkel  told her country’s lawmakers that she will back lower  interest rates  for emergency loans if Greece agrees to sell
state assets and Ireland backs a common corporate tax base in
the euro area.  EFG Eurobank Ergasias SA (EUROB)  , the
country’s second-largest lender, rose 2.9 percent to 4.68 euros.
Alpha Bank SA (ALPHA GA) surged 4.2 percent to 4.92 euros.  Piraeus Bank SA (TPEIR)   added 3.6 percent to 1.46 euros.    Opap SA (OPAP)   advanced 1.2 percent to 15.64 euros.
Europe’s biggest listed gambling company had its share price
estimate raised to 17.50 euros from 14 euros at Euroxx
Securities SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
